â™« <i>I've got a silly fair excuse</i> â™«

76
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:27,940
<i>[Murai in Love]</i>

77
00:04:29,010 --> 00:04:30,630
I will give you your results from the term-end exam.

78
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:33,520
I will give separate details to those who need extra lessons.
<i>[Episode 3: Happy Summer of Love]</i>

79
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,530
Make sure you attend.
<i>[Episode 3: Happy Summer of Love]</i>

80
00:04:35,530 --> 00:04:38,000
Miss? What's the schedule for the extra lessons?

81
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:42,010
You got a perfect grade, so you won't need extra lessons.

82
00:04:42,010 --> 00:04:44,450
Please come get them in numerical order.

83
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,930
<i>The day of freedom has finally come.</i>

84
00:04:46,930 --> 00:04:48,400
<i>Farewell, Murai.</i>

85
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,110
<i>Farewell, my students!</i>

86
00:04:50,110 --> 00:04:54,430
<i>If you're still alive, let's meet again in the second term!</i>

87
00:04:59,650 --> 00:05:02,340
The tenth day, right?

88
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:08,030
At last, the door to the underworld is before me...

89
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,860
How many days has it been since I got a call?

90
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:23,140
Apparently this is still a world tied to reality...

91
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,980
Or so I thought.

92
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,650
It seems like I was already in the middle of the underworld.
<i>[Dark Lord Hades]</i>

93
00:05:29,650 --> 00:05:30,880
Hello?

94
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,480
<i>Hey, it's me.</i>

95
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:35,500
<i>Are you ready for tomorrow's extra lesson?</i>

96
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:38,250
- Extra lesson?
- <i>The extra lesson.</i>

97
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:41,170
<i>I was just checking because I haven't heard from you.</i>

98
00:05:41,170 --> 00:05:44,710
<i>Don't tell me you haven't prepared anything.</i>

99
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,170
<i>[Summer Vacation Japanese History B Remedial Course Guide]</i>

100
00:05:46,170 --> 00:05:48,280
Crap!

101
00:05:50,540 --> 00:05:53,590
It's fine. I'm totally prepared for it.

102
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:56,430
<i>I'd strangle you if you weren't, you know.</i>

103
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,180
Damn it!

104
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:04,610
<i>[Supplementary Lesson Quiz]</i>

105
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:15,500
You seem tired.

106
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,610
Is the summer heat wearing you out?

107
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:20,670
Jeez! I told you not to come. Why are you here?

108
00:06:20,670 --> 00:06:23,290
I have something for you.

109
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:40,310
I got it through a friend.

110
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:44,050
<i>You used it as a disguise during an event, didn't you?</i>

111
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:47,040
- Are you trying to threaten me?
- No.

112
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,590
There's a flyer inside that.

113
00:06:54,730 --> 00:06:59,120
"Colorful Rainbow Happy Summer Festival"?

114
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:02,140
I don't understand what you're saying.

115
00:07:02,140 --> 00:07:05,200
Would you come to the summer festival with me?

116
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,970
I want to go to that festival with you.

117
00:07:10,110 --> 00:07:13,320
You and I are teacher and student.

118
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:17,250
You can wear that disguise during the festival.

119
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:19,530
<i>A masterful strategy...</i>

120
00:07:19,530 --> 00:07:22,490
<i>Is this the work of his adviser?</i>

121
00:07:22,490 --> 00:07:24,850
I wonder how this will play out...

122
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:28,060
War council! We're having a war council!

123
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:32,940
If she agrees to this, she'll cross the line she's drawn between teacher and student!

124
00:07:32,940 --> 00:07:35,740
It will inevitably come back to haunt her later!

125
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:37,520
I, however, want to let her go.

126
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,490
- Sir!
- This is for the princess!

127
00:07:39,490 --> 00:07:42,470
She can shut herself in her room and sacrifice herself to love...

128
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:47,020
But she must go outside to enjoy a real summer!

129
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:50,460
Don't hold a war council over such trivial matters.

130
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,960
Sir Hitotose!

131
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:55,560
The Lady has me!

132
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:58,260
What else could she need?

133
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:03,330
I'm sorry.

134
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:09,640
Unfortunately I already have plans on that day.

135
00:08:13,820 --> 00:08:17,180
You should go with your friends.

136
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,100
I will.

137
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,400
Then I'll see you in the second term.

138
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:29,320
Yes. Take care.

139
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,520
You, too!

140
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:34,970
Watch out for heat exhaustion.

141
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,290
<i>Good grief...</i>

142
00:08:39,290 --> 00:08:42,250
<i>A persistent one, isn't he?</i>

143
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:47,360
<i>[Colorful Rainbow Happy Summer Festival]</i>

144
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,340
Chi-chan!

145
00:08:54,150 --> 00:08:56,420
You came again.

146
00:08:56,420 --> 00:08:58,270
Are you sure? What about your training?

147
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:01,070
It's summer vacation, after all!

148
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:03,250
A summer festival, right?

149
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:06,920
We used to go when we were little. With the twins.

150
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:10,230
We did used to do that, didn't we?

151
00:09:10,230 --> 00:09:11,940
Are you going?

152
00:09:14,070 --> 00:09:18,580
There was someone I wanted to go with, but she said no.

153
00:09:20,590 --> 00:09:23,490
"Someone you wanted to go with"?

154
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:25,080
Yes.

155
00:09:26,610 --> 00:09:27,990
Who was it?

156
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:30,300
An older woman.

157
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:45,060
A woman?

158
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:48,380
I like her.

159
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:50,770
Since when?

160
00:09:50,770 --> 00:09:52,950
A long time.

161
00:09:52,950 --> 00:09:57,740
In elementary school, I...

162
00:09:57,740 --> 00:09:59,480
Man, you're as agile as ever!

163
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:02,120
I've never heard about this!

164
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:05,850
Because I've never told you about it.

165
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:13,560
Chi-chan... I can't stand.

166
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:14,610
I can't stand!

167
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:18,530
What? Did it hit you? Did your opponent's punch hit you?

168
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:20,600
Pat my head!

169
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:25,410
Like you did back then. Pat my head!

170
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:27,740
<i>You all alone there, Miss?
[Ten Years Ago]</i>

171
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,710
<i>Do you want to play with me?</i>

172
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:31,570
<i>- No!
- It's all right!</i>

173
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:33,610
<i>Stop!</i>

174
00:10:34,620 --> 00:10:37,240
<i>Let go of Yayo-chan!</i>

175
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,970
<i>Chi-chan!</i>

176
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:46,500
<i>There, there... There, there, Yayo.</i>

177
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:52,420
<i>After that day, I listened to my parents and continued training every single day.</i>

178
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:57,870
Even if creeps attacked me, I got strong enough to crush them!

179
00:10:57,870 --> 00:11:03,420
But no matter how strong I got, there was one thing I couldn't change.

180
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:07,970
I want to be your wife, Chi-chan!

181
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:09,880
I did my best!

182
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:13,400
I worked so, so hard to give up my strength

183
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:17,110
and become cute enough for you!

184
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:18,830
Yayo-chan...

185
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:23,800
I mean, "Colorful Rainbow Happy Summer Festival"?

186
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:28,920
"Colorful" and "rainbow" are redundant, and "happy" is just dumb. Who thought this up?

187
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:30,960
Tanaka?

188
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,390
Good afternoon.

189
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:35,730
What are you doing next Sunday?

190
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,770
We're short-staffed.
<i>[August 14 (Sunday)]</i>

191
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:44,830
Three guys going to a summer festival.

192
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:48,010
We're the coolest.

193
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:51,180
Tetsuko turned Murai down. We have to cheer him up too!

194
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:52,750
That's true.

195
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:54,410
Kiri? Hirai?

196
00:11:54,410 --> 00:11:57,740
- Sorry for the wait! Murai, you're here!
- What do you want me to do?

197
00:11:57,740 --> 00:12:00,630
- What do you want me to do?
- Want to go scoop goldfish?

198
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:03,040
What? Scoop goldfish?

199
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:05,570
Goldfish, goldfish, goldfish!

200
00:12:05,570 --> 00:12:07,350
Oh, this is my friend-

201
00:12:07,350 --> 00:12:10,710
I'm Fukunaga, Murai-kun's childhood friend.

202
00:12:11,450 --> 00:12:16,290
Well, hello! You're cute! Do you have a boyfriend? Want to go around the stalls with me?

203
00:12:16,290 --> 00:12:17,410
What?

204
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:20,460
Well, he already likes someone

205
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:25,380
so I guess this means I'll keep you company, instead.

206
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:29,430
Sorry, I'm not fond of flashly guys.

207
00:12:29,430 --> 00:12:33,590
Well, there's one other guy. What about him?

208
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:37,350
Hirai?

209
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:41,430
Hey, over here!

210
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:42,700
Watch it!

211
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:45,730
- What is it?
- You didn't mention her!

212
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:48,180
Sorry. She really wanted to come.

213
00:12:48,180 --> 00:12:51,430
Don't apologize! I need to give you a letter of commendation!

214
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:55,140
Today... my summer finally begins!

215
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,470
Oh, really?

216
00:12:56,470 --> 00:12:59,940
Do you know the person Chi-chan likes?

217
00:12:59,940 --> 00:13:02,140
And if I do?

218
00:13:02,140 --> 00:13:04,020
It doesn't matter.

219
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:08,410
Don't get in our way, alright?

220
00:13:08,410 --> 00:13:10,060
"Our"?

221
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,190
Sorry!

222
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:14,040
I mean, sorry that took so long! Let's go walk around!

223
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,250
Okay!

224
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:19,840
Don't go lumping you two together. I won't get in your way.

225
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:23,350
But his heart is a battleground.

226
00:13:24,050 --> 00:13:26,020
All right. Let's go to my family's stall.

227
00:13:26,020 --> 00:13:27,360
Yes, let's go.

228
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:28,440
Wait, Chi-chan!

229
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,300
- Gyoza, gyoza!
- Do you want to go get gyoza?

230
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,090
<i>[Colorful Rainbow Happy Summer Festival]</i>

231
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:38,310
- Hey. Thanks for making time for this.
- It's no trouble.

232
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:43,550
- It's a pain, but let's get going. The summer festival patrol.
- Yes!

233
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:45,570
That hurts, Dad! Stop!

234
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:48,100
My own son, ditching our stall!

235
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:50,150
What are you thinking, sticking your nose in Murai-kun's business?

236
00:13:50,150 --> 00:13:51,590
Hirai-kun, you go over here!

237
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:53,210
But I have nothing to do with this!

238
00:13:53,210 --> 00:13:55,390
You can attract some customers with your good looks!

239
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:57,520
Oh? What about Murai? Murai?

240
00:13:57,520 --> 00:14:00,220
He can't leave that girl alone!

241
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,840
- I'll help out, too.
- I will, too!

242
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:06,990
It's fine! It'll get cramped with too many people! Go walk around over there.

243
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:08,480
You two look cute together!

244
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:11,430
- Kiri, I'll do a loop, and then we'll swap.
- Okay.

245
00:14:11,430 --> 00:14:15,180
You'd better come back! In five minutes- No, one minute!

246
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:18,170
You don't need to come back!

247
00:14:18,930 --> 00:14:20,740
We'll make our rounds from the back then.

248
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:22,590
- All right. See you.
- See you around.

249
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:24,420
Let's go.

250
00:14:32,340 --> 00:14:35,230
Do you think patrol is a pain in the ass?

251
00:14:35,230 --> 00:14:37,470
No, not really.

252
00:14:37,470 --> 00:14:39,570
That's good then.

